&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You Will Make an Impact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the &lt;strong&gt;IT Support Analyst, &lt;/strong&gt;you will join our fast-paced, 24-hour operational manufacturing team. This role involves working in both indoor and outdoor environments across our Kermit and Monahans, Texas locations. If you are a quick learner with a passion for systems, networking, and desktop support, we want to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously develop expertise in systems and network administration to enhance performance and efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gain hands-on experience with industry-leading virtualization technologies such as Hyper-V, Veeam, and VMware, contributing to the optimization of virtual environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver responsive and effective end-user support through a ticketing system, phone, and direct requests, ensuring minimal disruption to operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Systems Administrators on diverse projects, providing valuable assistance in troubleshooting and system maintenance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and refine detailed documentation of processes and procedures to standardize workflows and improve knowledge sharing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively address after-hours IT requests, ensuring timely issue resolution and escalating complex problems as necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deploy and configure IT assets across enterprise environments, aligning technology with business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support backup and disaster recovery processes to maintain data integrity and business continuity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to provide desktop support for both local and remote staff in manufacturing (outdoors) and office environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with desktop software, networking (routers, switches), and troubleshooting IT issues both in person and remotely.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong multitasking skills in a fast-paced, high-energy environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel and work across multiple Texas locations (primarily Kermit and Monahans) with flexible, on-call availability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You Will Stand Out&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AAS in Computer Science or a related technical field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in IT support within a manufacturing setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with virtualization technologies and advanced networking systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team player with a positive, supportive attitude.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
